-- pd.package: FTD roboto package
name: fastn-community.github.io/roboto-font

This FTD font `roboto` package is for your ftd web projects. To Use this
roboto inside `FTD` project follow below instructions.

-- ds.h3: How to use roboto?

-- ds.code: Add this to your FASTN.ftd
lang: ftd

\-- fastn.dependency: fastn-community.github.io/roboto-font

-- ds.markdown: 

After adding roboto dependency inside you `FASTN.ftd` file, You need to add
roboto assets and import it inside you `ftd` file where you are using this
font for your custom font types. To include roboto into your `ftd` file
follow below instructions.

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd

\-- import: fastn-community.github.io/roboto-font/assets as roboto-assets


-- ds.h3: How to create a custom roboto type? 

-- ds.markdown: 

How to use `ftd.type` to create a custom font `types` using roboto? 

We don't recommend creating custom types. We recommend to use 
our [roboto-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/roboto-typography)

If you're using [roboto-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/roboto-typography) 
and still your designer has introduced new font size which is not included or 
part of our [roboto-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/roboto-typography) 
then only define custom types. 

We hope you shouldn't need to define a custom type.

Below is an example of creating a custom `ftd.type` using roboto.

-- ds.rendered:

-- ds.rendered.input:

\-- ftd.type roboto-size-12-desktop:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $roboto-assets.fonts.Roboto


\-- ftd.type roboto-size-12-mobile:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $roboto-assets.fonts.Roboto

\-- ftd.responsive-type roboto-size-12-400:
desktop: $roboto-size-12-desktop
mobile: $roboto-size-12-mobile

-- ds.rendered.output:

-- ftd.text: 
role: $roboto-size-12-400
color: $inherited.colors.text-strong

`font-size: 12px, font-weight: 400` 

